description:
Batch 3/5 — Observability (2 of 2)

Emit daemon events for individual agent lifecycle transitions:

- agent-spawned: { task_id, workflow_id, phase_id, pool_active, pool_size }
- agent-completed: { task_id, workflow_id, phase_id, duration_secs, outcome: advance/rework/fail, pool_active }
- agent-failed: { task_id, workflow_id, phase_id, error, pool_active }
- pool-backfill: { task_id, workflow_id, triggered_by: "agent-completion" | "housekeeping" }
- pool-full: { queued_count, active_count, pool_size } (emitted when work is available but pool is at capacity)

These events flow through the existing emit_daemon_event infrastructure and are visible via ao daemon events. Also enables future SSE/WebSocket streaming for the web UI.
